-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| About the development enviroment (installation details)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  > Windows:
      o Eclipse CDT Juno SR2 x64
          - Subclipse 1.8.x
          - Subclipse Client Adapter 1.8.x
          - Subversion JavaHL 1.7.x
      o MinGW x86
          - gcc 4.6.2
          - g++ 4.6.2
          - gdb 7.4
      o wxWidgets 2.8.12
  > Linux:
      o Eclipse CDT Juno SR2 x64
          - Subclipse 1.8.x
          - Subclipse Client Adapter 1.8.x
          - SVNKit 1.7.x
          - SVNKit Client Adapter 1.7.x
          - JNA Library 3.4.x
      o Built in tools
          - gcc 4.6.3
          - g++ 4.6.3
          - gdb 7.4
          - make 3.81

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| Build targets
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  > Windows:
      o debug-win32 (using MinGW x86)
      o release-win32 (using MinGW x86)
  > Linux:
      o debug-linux64 (using Linux x64 tools)
      o release-linux64 (using Linux x64 tools)
      
  Note:
  If you want to add other build targets, right click on the project go to
  Properties, select C/C++ Build, choose Manage Configurations... and add your
  debug and release configurations using the naming convention build-platform.
  In the Create New Configuration window you have to choose the
  Import predefined radio button, then select your installed compiler to import
  the settings of current configuration.
  